<ul>
  <li><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4YtK9YXaHvQdzV0aUJ5MEhWRUE">Download the Xplorer 360 Extreme2 program and Partition2.bin files.</a></li>
  <li>Extract the program and bin file. I would recommend to your desktop for easy access.</li>
  <li>Right click on Xplorer360 Extreme2.exe and click the option ‚ÄúRun as administrator‚Äù.</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/hjrt4qzgi/image/upload/v1/images/projects/599b221c83acf_ss.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Click on the Drive tab &gt; Open &gt; Harddrive or Memcard‚Ä¶</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/hjrt4qzgi/image/upload/v1/images/projects/599b22394d902_ss.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Click on the Drive tab &gt; Restore Partition 2</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/hjrt4qzgi/image/upload/v1/images/projects/599b224980e2a_ss.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Using this newly opened window, navigate to the Partition2.bin, select it and click the open button.</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/hjrt4qzgi/image/upload/v1/images/projects/599b2257ad421_ss.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>You will now see a progress bar, and once it is complete it will either say it has finished OR the program will crash! This is ok, as the program has finished it‚Äôs process.</li>
  <li>Put the hard drive back in to your Xbox 360 console, turn it on, and play an Xbox original game. It might prompt you for a small 5mb patch. Go ahead and download/install the patch.</li>
</ul>

<p>You are now ready to play Xbox original games on your Xbox 360! Any questions or comments feel free to leave a comment below or check out my other videos on my youtube channel or post in our forums for support.</p>
